Class ComponentModelArchitectureHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.plugins.devs.architectures.ComponentModelArchitectureHelper

  • public abstract class ComponentModelArchitectureHelper
extends java.lang.Object
    The class ComponentArchitectureHelper defines code that is used by component simulation architectures to create and interconnect simulation models held by BCM components.

      • connectManagementPort

        public static SimulationManagementOutboundPort connectManagementPort(fr.sorbonne_u.components.AbstractComponent portCreator,
                                                                     java.lang.String modelURI,
                                                                     CyPhyReflectionOutboundPort rop)
        create, connect and return the simulation management outbound port for the component creator (which executes this code); the returned port is connected with the simulation management inbound port of the component to which the reflection outbound port rop is itself connected.

        Contract

         pre     portCreator != null
 pre     modelURI != null && !modelURI.isEmpty()
 pre     rop != null && rop.connected()
 post    ret != null && ret.connected()
        Parameters:
        portCreator - port creator component executing this code.
        modelURI - URI of the model held by the creator component.
        rop - reflection outbound port connected to component holding the model modelURI.
        Returns:
        the simulation management outbound port held by portCreator
